                        "page": "1888"
                      },
                      "date": 2011
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                " 3 points with chemical separation for 55Mn(p,n)55Fe"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "2GERJUL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Two cyclotrons of the Research Centre",
                " Julich, namely, the Compact Cyclotron CV28 and the",
                " Injector of COSY. The primary projectile energies used",
                " were 19.0 and 45.0 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "High-purity manganese-dioxide powder(99.99%,supplied",
                " by Sigma-Aldrich, Germany) and high-purity foils of",
                " Mn, Ni, Al,Ti and Cu (99.999%,supplied by Goodfellow,",
                " England) were used.",
                "In two experiments thin Mn foils (10 mu-m thick) were",
                " used. The exact thickness of each foil was obtained by",
                " weighing and determining the area. In several other",
                " experiments sedimented MnO2 samples were used. The",
                " thickness of the MnO2 layer was 5-20 mg/cm2. It was",
                " homogeneous and mechanically stable. The layer was",
                " covered by a 10 mu-m thick and 16 mm in diameter",
                " Al foil. Thus each sample consisted of an Al-MnO2-Al",
                " sandwich."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two stacks of Mn foils and several stacks of",
                " the sedimented manganese-dioxide samples together with",
                " the absorbers and monitors were irradiated"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The absolute efficiency curves of the detector",
                " were determined at source-detector distances of 5, 10,",
                " 15, 20 and 30 cm using gamma-ray standards supplied by",
                " the PTB Braunschweig or Amersham International."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SILI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Used for X-ray spectrometry. It had an active",
                " diameter of 4 mm, a depth 4.59 mm and was covered",
                " by a 12.7 mm thick Be film."
              ]
            }
          ],
